Gorka: This needs to be added to this command to allow deletion with both cascade and force, which our API now allows.'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2017-08-23 14:58:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

We also did have some discussion about moving away from force-delete here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/320052/1/specs/newton/delete-parameters.rst'}, {'account_id': 25456, 'date': '2017-08-25 09:16:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

> We have force-delete command, adding these options to delete
 > instead to force-delete will not help our usability.
 > 
 > If we want to stop using force-delete in favor of using delete
 > --force then that's a broader discussion.

Gorka,
Now, both cascade and force params have been implemented for deleting a volume in Cinder.
I think using the params to delete is much better, we can delete a volume whaterver the force param or the cascade param or even the future new added params by using different params.
Also, this can lessen our Cinder API management."}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2017-08-25 12:51:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

OK, so the commit message needs some work, because what it's saying is incorrect, but the bigger problem (and I hope this doesn't merge now that I've removed the -2) is that in terms of usability this is a nightmare.

If you are running Newton and using v3 api you cannot do:

 cinder delete --force

Yo somehow have to know that you have to do

 cinder force-delete

But if you are running Ocata or later you can use any of those two commands.

I believe we need a consistent mechanism that will work regardless of the v3 microversion and will only fail if you try to do --cascade and --force on the same command prior to 3.23."}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2017-09-07 22:32:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: Code-Review+2

I'd like to see this implemented and the force-delete command removed entirely.  If we deprecate it now, we can remove it in a year"}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2017-09-08 09:06:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

So apparently everyone is cool with merging something that is fundamentally broken from a usability point of view...'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2017-10-25 17:54:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

I'm not sure how this is broken usability-wise.  What I had in mind was jgriffith's plan above: migrate toward this and ditch "force-delete", because it's not needed as a separate operation.  This isn't any more complex than most other changes that occur with microversions and API changes.'}, {'account_id': 25456, 'date': '2017-10-26 02:22:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Commit message was updated.'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2017-10-26 13:25:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10: Code-Review+2

I agree with Eric's last comment. I'd like to see us go this direction."}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2017-11-03 10:56:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2017-11-07 10:16:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

I insist this is completely wrong from a user's point of view.  It should always be possible to call "cinder delete --force" in the command line, regardless of what API endpoint ends up being called.

The user calls "cinder delete --force" and cinderclient should either call the old "os-force_delete" method if API is older than v3.23 and call delete with the "force" parameter set to "true" otherwise.

This would provide a consistent interface instead of making the user know when it's ok to call "cinder delete --force".

With this patch if you are running Newton and using v3 api you cannot do:
 cinder delete --force
You somehow have to know that you have to do
 cinder force-delete
But if you are running Ocata or later you can use any of those two commands.'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2017-11-07 14:19:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

> I insist this is completely wrong from a user's point of view.  It
 > should always be possible to call "cinder delete --force"

I agree, but, what we were previously doing was also wrong (having a separate force-delete verb), and this is going in the right direction, so I still think it's a win.

How bad this approach is depends a lot on your guess as to how often people would combine a Queens cinderclient with a Newton deployment.  I don't know the answer to that.

 > The user calls "cinder delete --force" and cinderclient should
 > either call the old "os-force_delete" method if API is older than
 > v3.23 and call delete with the "force" parameter set to "true"
 > otherwise.

Can this be mapped just by checking cs.api_version in the do_delete method?

I don't mind trying to add this if we have some infrastructure in place to do it.'}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2017-11-08 09:56:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

> > I insist this is completely wrong from a user's point of view. 
 > It
 > > should always be possible to call "cinder delete --force"
 > 
 > I agree, but, what we were previously doing was also wrong (having
 > a separate force-delete verb), and this is going in the right
 > direction, so I still think it's a win.
 > 

In my experience it pays to do it right the first time, as it's unlikely that somebody else will improve this afterwards.

 > How bad this approach is depends a lot on your guess as to how
 > often people would combine a Queens cinderclient with a Newton
 > deployment.  I don't know the answer to that.
 > 

There are other cases were this would come into play, as you could be using Queens and call the client with the vanilla v3.0 microversion.


 > > The user calls "cinder delete --force" and cinderclient should
 > > either call the old "os-force_delete" method if API is older than
 > > v3.23 and call delete with the "force" parameter set to "true"
 > > otherwise.
 > 
 > Can this be mapped just by checking cs.api_version in the do_delete
 > method?
 > 

That was my suggestion, you always accept --force and then decide which REST API method to call.'}, {'account_id': 25456, 'date': '2017-11-09 10:36:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

This issue should be discussed in the weekly meeting. I think we had better provide a unique interface for deleting whihcever API version, the previous implements for --force and force-delete needs to be merged for one API.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2017-11-16 23:37:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

I'd agree with Gorka, additionally the seperate `force-delete` command is silly and frankly it doesn't work anyway... but that's another rant.

I like the idea of just adding `--force` to the client and having it "do the right thing".  It's a much more sane user experience and not nearly as maddening as trying to juggle/deal with 100 microversions.'}, {'account_id': 170, 'date': '2017-11-18 00:53:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

Agree with john and gorka. Not sure how else the weekly meeting discussion will go.'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2017-11-29 21:56:21.000000000', 'content': 'Removed Code-Review+2 by Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>
'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2017-11-29 22:59:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

Just to clarify, my thinking was that the --force flag is great (how a new verb `force-delete` made it in is maddening), but point is/was don't mess with versions in the client like this.

Just add the --force to both V2 and V3 shell and if the servers API Version (or MV) isn't available, be smart in the client and sort it out.  The point being don't make the client more convoluted and difficult to use than necessary, and most of all don't introduce a guessing game for users to figure out what they can and can't do.

If you were to modify this to just support "cinder delete --force" in both V2 and V3.x and hide the versioning stuff it would in my opinion fix some of our past mistakes here and I would be happy to up-vote and argue for it to be merged.'}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2017-11-29 23:16:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

I think we should go with what John, Gorka and Mike are suggesting.  No hurry here, lets do it right.'}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2018-01-17 23:48:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

Should this change be abandoned?'}, {'account_id': 25456, 'date': '2018-01-18 00:13:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

> Should this change be abandoned?

Yes, I will abondon it right now.'}, {'account_id': 25456, 'date': '2018-01-18 00:13:30.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-06-28 09:19:59.000000000', 'message': 'Fix force delete volume in v3.23

Cinder support force delete volumes, However, in cinderclient, no comand
line support this feature. This patch is to add force delete in cinderclient.

  # cinder help delete
  usage: cinder delete [--cascade <False|True>] [--force <False|True>]
                       <volume> [<volume> ...]
  Removes one or more volumes.
  Positional arguments:
    <volume> Name or ID of volume or volumes to delete.
  Optional arguments:
    --cascade <False|True>
             Remove any snapshots along with volume. Default=False.
    --force <False|True> Force to delete the volume. Default=False.

Add the force param and it will be passed through cinderclient to Cinder API,
if the version is v3.23, then the param force will take effect.

Change-Id: I2056b8d94bbf29d2f6943de7612954147a0e8cde
Closes-Bug: #1700927
'}, {'created': '2017-06-29 08:19:25.000000000', 'message': 'Add force delete volume in v3.23

commit_message:
Support "--force" param to delete volume in v3.23

Cinder supports delete volumes by using force param, However, in
cinderclient, no comand line support this feature. This patch is
to add "--force" param to delete in cinderclient.

Add the "--force" param and it will be passed through cinderclient
to Cinder API, if the version is v3.23, then the force param would
take effect.


Implements: bp volume-delete-parameters
Change-Id: I2056b8d94bbf29d2f6943de7612954147a0e8cde

commit_message:
Containerize multinode-3nodes

This patch will force the 3nodes job to be containerized, like all jobs
should be in Queens.
Another patch in tripleo-quickstart will update the featureset.
Also moving Clustercheck service where MariaDB & Pacemaker run.
Also remove Heat since we'll run Tempest.

Change-Id: I31e1fe29491d2cbaa8ed9cd35ee84bbb1d455154

commit_message:
Consume blacklisted_ip_addresses in workflows

The ceph-ansible and skydive workflows now consumes the
blacklisted_ip_addresses input.

The enable_ssh_admin workflow is modified to consume a list of
ip addresses and only enable ssh on the given set of addresses.

Change-Id: I4255739c852409fb8e170a9913fe7ad810711734
Depends-On: Ic158171c629e82892e480f1e6903a67457f86064
Closes-Bug: #1743046

commit_message:
Fix BadRequest for 'null' metadata and group_specs

Before schema validation patches [1] and [2] merged, it was allowed
to pass metadata and group_specs as null but with these patches 400
BadRequest is returned to user.

This patch fixes this issue by allowing group_specs and metadata to
be null in request_body.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/528631/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/519643/

Change-Id: If207877811a5c331c28fc853cf233758a1743903
Closes-Bug: #1742938

commit_message:
polling: iter randomly over sources and pollsters when polling

By polling in a random order sources and pollster, it is more likely than
different Ceilometer agents will not hit the same e.g. API endpoint at the same
time.

Change-Id: I754a67a8adfb97f8950c666f9aab3bc3d435e2ac

[{'created': '2018-01-11 19:36:31.000000000', 'message': 'Switched rally job from q-qos to neutron-qos

There is no functional difference between two in how devstack plugin for
neutron is implemented; but using neutron-* name pattern allows gate to
enable lib/neutron instead of lib/neutron-legacy devstack library to
deploy neutron services, which is the plan for all next releases.

Depends-On: I2fbd7649b6ef312940dca704ed3ebdb1e2e93576
Change-Id: I5df0da31a137b49f24b1337cfc16e938f8de9f9f
'}]
commit_message:
Switched rally job from q-qos to neutron-qos

There is no functional difference between two in how devstack plugin for
neutron is implemented; but using neutron-* name pattern allows gate to
enable lib/neutron instead of lib/neutron-legacy devstack library to
deploy neutron services, which is the plan for all next releases.

Depends-On: I2fbd7649b6ef312940dca704ed3ebdb1e2e93576
Change-Id: I5df0da31a137b49f24b1337cfc16e938f8de9f9f

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

OK, Brian.

My story is:

1) I found a bug, tried to fix it. It was unsuccessful. Then I found function uninstall_flows in the master branch and replace delete_flows to uninstall_flows. Then I found patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/406731/7/neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py This patch does the same.

2) The next step is awareness of that there is no uninstall_flows implementation in the stable/ocata branch

3) I decided to implement this function (uninstall_flows) and copy code from master branch:
https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/7c1e21a3f35e80e176dfc025eb6f4a0024cb137c/neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/openflow/native/ofswitch.py#L108

I can see three changes - one is the original to master, the other a stable/ocata backport that merged in July.  The third is this change, which has the same commit message, but has none of the same code.  Merging this would then have two changes that look the same from the commit message viewpoint, but not what they do.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/437952/ seems like the change to master you are trying to do a partial backport of, correct?  "delete_flows shall only touch flows with the bridge cookie"

So I'm not saying the code shouldn't be backported, just that all the references (commit message, cherry-pick ID, etc) seen wrong, and will only lead to more confusion as this continues downstream.'}, {'account_id': 27530, 'date': '2018-01-09 09:12:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hi Brian!

I guess that I have several options:
1) Filing a new bug
2) Make a cherry-pick of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/437952/
3) Just change commit message
4) Make a new review

What options do you advise to do? I'm confused of this problem

I think you need to explain several things:

- why is the patch carrying commit message from seemingly unrelated change?
- why do you backport just pieces of the other patch, leaving most of it out? Is it safe to do?
- it would be nice to see a failure mode from user perspective captured either here or in the bug itself, so that we can understand whether the backport should be allowed to merge in stable/ocata branch that is currently in Support Phase II meaning that only high impact user visible bug fixes are allowed to merge.

Once we have all this clarified, I think we should be able to understand our next steps here.

commit_message:
ovs-agent: Clear in_port=ofport flow earlier

This is the minimum change to pass tempest's
test_update_instance_port_admin_state test. Alternatively, the delete_flows
could be changed to just deal with drop_port flows, which can affect
3rd party codes.

Closes-Bug: #1559920
(cherry picked from commit c54c5791b43deada9936f0c9c5d8b681a3216893)

Change-Id: I28652286c7c0622ee69159b505ec6e46a911a2c5

Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

commit_message:
Use wraps decorator

Use wraps decorator from functools library.
This calls the update_wrapper method from functools
which sets these built-in values to those of the
wrapped function.

Change-Id: I3df3d4e8dbbbbcf384436441349c05386f2b0743

[{'created': '2018-01-08 08:25:15.000000000', 'message': 'Switch to use ovsdbapp.api.API

In neutron.agent.ovsdb.impl_vsctl.OvsdbVsctl inherited from deprecated
neutron.agent.ovsdb.api.API class.
Currently instead of this deprecated class ovsdbapp.api.API should be
used and this patch changes it.

Change-Id: I7ffc0d2e8f590795000ba9891f6b2ae62a05fee6
'}, {'created': '2018-01-08 11:14:15.000000000', 'message': 'Switch to use directly ovsdbapp.api module

In neutron.agent.ovsdb.api module there were some deprecated
"redirections" to classes from ovsdbapp.api module.

commit_message:
Switch to use directly ovsdbapp.api module

In neutron.agent.ovsdb.api module there were some deprecated
"redirections" to classes from ovsdbapp.api module.

Now those redirections are removed and classes from ovsdbapp.api are
used directly.

Change-Id: I7ffc0d2e8f590795000ba9891f6b2ae62a05fee6

commit_message:
Fix zookeeper devstack installation

The zookeeper devstack installation had few issues:
1. The configured port was ignored, and DF could not
connect to the DB
2. The systemd service file is already created by
the installation itself

Co-Authored-By: Shachar Snapiri <shachar.snapiri@huawei.com>

Change-Id: I82bc200181768a7065adce7a7fc5999b4ae97cb3

commit_message:
Do not validate root partition size for whole disk images in iscsi deploy

On whole disk images a root partition is already created and populated, so
validating its size makes no sense. We don't do it for direct deploy.

Change-Id: I7a4114979afb310aeb77f99fbcf09ef7c54862d6
Closes-Bug: #1742451

commit_message:
Base mechanism for full sync

This patch introduce a base class containing for all drivers. This
class is responsible for returning all resources of a specific
types.

Change-Id: I6e855422ce9da70c333013985b7d25a2a63bb658
Partial-bug: #1713697

commit_message:
Call "openstack overcloud container image" only once

Thanks to the fix for bug #1738663 it is no longer necessary to run
prepare separately to generate the environment file and the images
file.

Change-Id: Ice0fcb4e6b8f5f18694d989f5152cb23a3d88569
Related-Bug: #1738663

commit_message:
Force maintenance task on HUP on the worker

When JournalPeriodicProccesor gets a HUP it will now call a forced run
of the maintenance task. This can be useful to do a full sync on demand,
like in a deployment of ODL.

Change-Id: I0936a63b07982d8cb19687a63a0dc47684887002

subject: Removing groups scope from all to baremetal in baremetal pre-install task under bootstrap-server

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
VMAX driver - Errors extending replicated volumes

When attempting to extend multiple volumes concurrently, the operation
can fail due to insufficient locking on the RDF group. Additionally,
attempting to delete a volume after an earlier failure can fail as the
code does not check if the volume is already suspended. We also cannot
support extending SRDF/Metro volumes. This patch rectifies these issues.

Change-Id: Ib30f2a8f0a710f01ecb55ed753ecc41dbcdaad18
Closes-Bug: 1735456

[{'created': '2018-01-15 16:09:42.000000000', 'message': 'Replace validate-ipmi by enbaling tripleo-validations role

This review remove the validate-ipmi call in the baremetal
undercloud playbook and enables the tripleo-validations
role when jobs are not running upstream.

Note that the validate-ipmi role still needs to be deleted.
It has not been deleted in this review as others teams may
still be using it.

commit_message:
Replace validate-ipmi by enabling tripleo-validations role

This review removes the validate-ipmi call in the baremetal
undercloud playbook and enables the tripleo-validations
role when jobs are not running upstream.

Note that the validate-ipmi role still needs to be deleted.
It has not been deleted in this review as others teams may
still be using it.

Change-Id: I732d7f1cf82471f375c1fa41d94828f6a43b243a
Closes-Bug:1743403

commit_message:
Run test_mtu with vlan and vxlan

This should make it work for linuxbridge job flavour too. Linuxbridge
doesn't support GRE but VXLAN and VLAN only. We can switch from GRE to
VLAN in general case because VLAN doesn't consume any bytes from the
frame for its header, while VXLAN does, so resulting MTUs should be
expected to be different.

Closes-Bug: #1742197
Change-Id: I3e37396228ebda4590c4e07c43dcb7898541409c

commit_message:
Default empty map for docker_config steps

In the event a step has no services defined, we must still write the
config, as this is needed if services are disabled on update such that
a step becomes empty - we must run paunch on every step or the cleanup
of the "old" services does not happen.

Closes-Bug: 1742915
Change-Id: Iee01002f56b5311560557f2bf6f053601b9d43d7

commit_message:
Also pass blacklisted hostnames

Workflows may need access to the list of blacklisted hostnames so they
can filter on that value. This change adds that input to the workflow
execution environment.

Change-Id: I41de32b324a406633699d17933ae05417b28c57b
Partial-Bug: #1743046

commit_message:
Remove irrelevant-files for tempest-full

Several projects have irrelevant files listed for the tempest-full
job, but these are not used when the job is added through a template.

Common file exclusions are being added in
I6ce094be98a066b4c7ef6a0b7687cf2beb171a13, but the files listed in
project-config should be removed anyway to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: I9dcbf219383bea24b2e5e3516e72e606e9e0d2f8

commit_message:
WIP: Avoid job polling

We're doing polling when waiting for asynchronous WMI jobs to
complete. This is quite inefficient, doing a WMI query once every
0.1 seconds.

In order to avoid this, we're switching to WMI events.

This approach uses a daemon worker, catching all job events and
delivering them to subscribers.

Change-Id: I90d7a4e1c11a50bb470317661c6746d0f621d693

commit_message:
Append docker-ha.yaml conditionally.

The overcloud upgrade command will append
docker-ha.yaml env variable only if pacemaker
was deployed in the initial command. This same
condition was missed in the case of the converge
step command.

Change-Id: I05dd9a9a8ff2c033a8b3ec8716860153de2edda2

commit_message:
Correct erroneous upgrade tasks.

After merging [0], the step for each upgrade_task
is now handled in a 'when' condition. This patch
corrects some templates which where not following
that logic or had some syntax error.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/510902/

Change-Id: I5e42fa6b3d84ad6e0163900ee8146fd224fb5103

This aligns with the overcloud deploy, and enables faster testing

Change-Id: I0e44b1aa1be3436990053a665478c92e91856dee

commit_message:
Add -r/--roles-file option to undercloud deploy

This aligns with the overcloud deploy, and enables faster testing
with a customized roles_data.yaml (e.g one with a small number of
services).

Change-Id: I0e44b1aa1be3436990053a665478c92e91856dee

commit_message:
Passes NodeDataLookup to ceph-ansible workflow

Per-node customizations were only dumped as hieradata, so the
ceph-ansible workflow could not consume them.
This change passes the structure to the mistral workflow so that it
can consume the data and populate the inventory accordingly.

Change-Id: Ie7a9f10f0c821b8c642494a4d3933b2901f39d40
Depends-On: Ia23825aea938f6f9bcf536e35cad562a1b96c93b
Closes-Bug: #1736707
(cherry picked from commit 1971e7b049f13a8a2d45fb77412ff1a87ca043c2)

commit_message:
Fix openstackdocstheme options for api-ref

Initialize the parameter for current openstackdocstheme so that report a
bug feature works and displays all parameter including git URL and SHA.

We need to add openstackdocstheme as extension so that the parameter are
properly initialized. html_context is not needed anymore. The display of
time of last commit is done by openstackdocstheme.

Closes-Bug: #1743728
Change-Id: I415cacbf0d8d93ad45cc317ab3552a83d3cf69de

commit_message:
Do not validate root partition size for whole disk images in iscsi deploy

On whole disk images a root partition is already created and populated, so
validating its size makes no sense. We don't do it for direct deploy.

Change-Id: I7a4114979afb310aeb77f99fbcf09ef7c54862d6
Closes-Bug: #1742451
(cherry picked from commit a7623d92dc4d7c7bcc436656b93c8fe963e79bfd)

commit_message:
Configure log extension for ovs scenario job only

Current implementation of the agent l2 extension is not compatible with
linuxbridge. More work should happen before it's possible to enable it
back.

Related-Bug: #1743463

commit_message:
Add pycodestyle

pep8 was renamed to pycodestyle, so allow that one in order to
be able to transition to it.

The depends-on remove pyflake mentions as most projects adopted
flake8/hacking, we don't need to allow explicit dependencies
on the tools integrated by flake8 (mccabe, pycodestyle/pep8, pyflakes).

Cleanup those from the tests/ files to avoid grep'ing finding them.

Depends-On: I12b5e114c5c6783e9da5cca2818ac9266a00fc87
Depends-On: Ib145e2afa97f441c07fada9c30f0f0e2410870ae
Depends-On: Id44c90ddd4a8a2204fd7ce600097bafbc9469993

Change-Id: If9f30bf39143d5e6fefca794385cafc4456d2197

commit_message:
Migrate to keystoneauth identity cli opts.

Use keystoneauth1 to parse keystone authentication arguments. Previously
these arguments are parsed in the different service clients seperately.
Use keystoneauth1 instead will make this consistent across projects and
less error-prone.

This change is inspired by NovaClient.

Co-Authored-By: Morgan Fainberg <morgan.fainberg@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: David Hu <david.hu@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>

Closes-Bug: #1734945

Change-Id: I3c5141eeddd3747ff542e95b04e4848470ad9508
Signed-off-by: Zhao Chao <zhaochao1984@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Transform rescue/unrescue instance notifications

The rescue (instance.rescue.start and instance.rescue.end) and unrescue
(instance.unrescue.start and instance.unrescue.end) notifications are
transformed to the versioned framework.

This patch also fixes the power state of the server
when unrescuing it with the fake compute driver.

Co-Authored-By: Takashi Natsume <natsume.takashi@lab.ntt.co.jp>
Change-Id: Ib1d03c6d693e3b04886c638c956e35809fed8fc2
Implements: bp versioned-notification-transformation-queens
Closes-Bug: #1742133

commit_message:
Add more reasons to skip sharder probe tests

Sharder probe tests make assertions about sharding state that assume
default batch sizes, so skip if they are configured differently.

Change-Id: I597c695c18b43fc68995700be4857a65396476eb

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-01-16 09:10:01.000000000', 'message': 'Add status='ACTIVE' when using changes-since as filter

updated_at field may haven't been set at the point in the boot
process where build_request still exists, so filter by
{'changes-since': '2051-01-01T12:34:00Z'} may get server that is
"at the point in the boot process where build_request still exists",
and so the testcase may accidentally fail if there are other
testcases running at same time with pre-provisoned credentials.

This is to add status='ACTIVE' along with changes-since as filter.

Change-Id: Ieb0fd67ac9d691b53c1275166bdb0395d1570662
'}]
commit_message:
Add status='ACTIVE' when using changes-since as filter

updated_at field may haven't been set at the point in the boot
process where build_request still exists, so filter by
{'changes-since': '2051-01-01T12:34:00Z'} may get server that is
"at the point in the boot process where build_request still exists",
and so the testcase may accidentally fail if there are other
testcases running at same time with pre-provisoned credentials.

This is to add status='ACTIVE' along with changes-since as filter.

Change-Id: Ieb0fd67ac9d691b53c1275166bdb0395d1570662

commit_message:
[envs] Add OpenStack platform (part 2)

- Add OpenStack platform
- Fix EnvManager.destroy() method
- Unify traceback information, use always lists
  this is important because otherwise we can't use jsonschema
  for validation
- Add base class for testing of platforms that simplifies
  and unfifes checking schema

Co-Authored-By: Andrey Kurilin <andr.kurilin@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I83369e899a8b8609a8cd1e77b895d3a1ef8ae3e4

commit_message:
Check for security group correctness

This patch is updating networking-ovn to check for correctness when
creating and deleting security groups.

Note that, networking-ovn doesn't care about updates on security groups
so the patch only cares about whether the security group exist or not.

Change-Id: I2add7ba1eb989fd585792c751cba4ec87f3c4974

commit_message:
Add condition to create container images download script.

It is also interesting for the role to support
the option of passing by an already existing
script that handles the container images downloading.

By adding this conditional we avoid rewritting the
content of the passed script when setting the var
to false.

Change-Id: I8b82071dfa7d440c7c840ffb9bcdf006843b6d97

commit_message:
Avoid retrieving IP from a missing bridge

On hosts that do not have any containers (ie. computes) network bridges
are not needed and may introduce some unwanted overhead. This
configuration was possible until Mitaka, but broke with the
dynamic-address-fact.yml tasks in Newton.

This change checks if the bridge actually exists and otherwise uses the
IP configured in the inventory instead.

Change-Id: I23668429a19f00f520ac18c76254e83708778d5a
(cherry picked from commit ea32c3da767d156dc851abd9d2b5121375b760e8)

commit_message:
Support template functions

Support functions in version 2 of Vitrage templates. The first supported
function is get_attr(entity, attr_name), and it can be used only in
execute_mistral action.

Change-Id: I89ad0c7b7efcd07f1b49fc5603b0854d7f6730e6
Implements: blueprint refactor-execute-mistral-definition

commit_message:
Add ability to manage non-inventory hosts

We may want to load balance to existing services that we aren't managing
via ansible. Currently the hosts have to exist in the inventory in order
to add a VIP for these hosts, this patch adds the ability to set the
hostnames and addresses of the hosts manually when they aren't in the
ansible inventory.

Additionally, this patch adds a test for both the group method and the
host_lists method.

Change-Id: Ida66f401d8320d9bf14eac9b8014124631978808
(cherry picked from commit d2b2492c16711dbf1971ef513bcd43d33339cf38)

commit_message:
Adds TLS support to configuring OVS with OpenDaylight

Enables configuring OVS with SSL configuration, as well as setting
OVS managers and ODL check url to use SSL/TLS.  Each OVS will also
register their certificate with OpenDaylight's truststore.

Partially-Implements: blueprint opendaylight-ssl-support

Depends-On: Ic026ee0bc4f385e0f8cd7076b3044feeb935ae45

Change-Id: I719e8dddbd00d19fd8e1bd2a20dabd600b7b9d1c
Signed-off-by: Tim Rozet <trozet@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add ability to manage non-inventory hosts

We may want to load balance to existing services that we aren't managing
via ansible. Currently the hosts have to exist in the inventory in order
to add a VIP for these hosts, this patch adds the ability to set the
hostnames and addresses of the hosts manually when they aren't in the
ansible inventory.

Additionally, this patch adds a test for both the group method and the
host_lists method.

Change-Id: Ida66f401d8320d9bf14eac9b8014124631978808
(cherry picked from commit d2b2492c16711dbf1971ef513bcd43d33339cf38)
(cherry picked from commit edd3bf5e2144308a2c5de02f077d21a68f6c2305)
